## Bug Fixes (Post-Overhaul)
[X] Bug: Charts not showing — chart_paths not propagated after removing Chart: lines
    Root cause: analytics agent returned string, not dict; chart paths were extracted via regex from text, but text no longer has Chart: lines.
    Fix: Added `last_chart_paths` attribute to DataAnalyticsAgent; orchestrator reads it after calling the agent.
[X] Bug: Journal d'analyse shows "Analyse en cours" — trace steps actually ARE stored correctly but user may have been viewing stale cached page or loading state
    Verified: stored chat_history JSON has 6 trace steps with status "done". Frontend should render them.
[X] Bug: Internal table names (gld_dim_*) leak into stored messages — _sanitize_response was only applied to HTTP response, not to persisted messages.
    Fix: Applied _sanitize_response in _assistant_message_from_result before storing.

## Follow-Up Flow Fixes — COMPLETED
[X] Bug 1/8/9: Prediction agent never triggered — reordered _classify_instant (prediction keywords > follow-up pinning > years-outside-range), added accent normalization, fixed Layer 2 override
[X] Bug 2: Prediction context blind — orchestrator now passes actual_pred_message with history; PredictionAgent._resolve_implicit_refs extracts voie context
[X] Bug 3: Analytics KPI fast-path skipped history — both try_official_kpi_answer and kpi_cache.try_answer now append to conversation_history
[X] Bug 4: Classifier cache cross-pollution — cache key now includes conversation_id
[X] Bug 5: conversation_log truncation increased from 500 → 800 chars
[X] Bug 7: Removed unreachable dead code blocks in server.py (/api/chat and /api/insights)
All 22 unit tests + 11 live integration tests pass.

## Agentic Flow Redesign — Plan-Execute-Review-Humanize — COMPLETED
[X] Phase 1: Triage Node (orchestration/triage.py) — complexity assessment, deterministic fast-path + LLM fallback
[X] Phase 2: Planner Node (orchestration/planner.py) — structured plan generation with LLM + deterministic fallback
[X] Phase 3: Executor Node (orchestration/executor.py) — tool-calling loop wrapping SQL/search/RAG/prediction/chart
[X] Phase 4: Reviewer Node (orchestration/reviewer.py) — reflection loop with heuristic + LLM quality check
[X] Phase 5: Humanizer End-Node (orchestration/humanizer.py) — warm conversational tone for all responses
[X] Phase 6: Graph Runner (orchestration/graph.py) + wired into orchestrator._route_internal via USE_NEW_FLOW flag
[X] Phase 7: 51 unit tests (tests/test_orchestration_flow.py) — all passing
Feature flag: USE_NEW_FLOW=true (default) in settings.py enables new flow; false falls back to legacy.
Key insight: smart_search uses analysis_type param (not search_type). ResearcherAgent attrs: self.searcher, self.rag.
